Larval case (
Figs 14–15
): length 2.5–3 mm (n = 10 ), constructed of silk and transversally arranged sponge spicules. Larval case cylindrical, with openings at both ends; can be enveloped by the sponge colony. In the pupal stage, both ends are closed and case is attached to the substrate by silk (
Fig. 16
).
